HEADWORD: Grillroom
<hw>Grill"room`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A room
specially fitted for broiling food, esp. one in a restaurant, hotel, or
clubhouse, arranged for prompt service.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a restaurant where food is cooked on a grill.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> grill.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

